The article discusses the importance of the arts and humanities in our society, particularly in times of crisis. It highlights how the arts provide solace, understanding, and healing, as well as amplify diverse voices and messages. The COVID-19 pandemic has had a devastating impact on the arts and cultural sectors, leading to high unemployment rates and closures of venues. The article emphasizes the need for the creative economy and cultural sector to recover for the nation to fully heal and thrive. The Biden administration is committed to supporting the arts community through funding programs and partnerships. The arts also play a role in education, communication, and healing, addressing inequities, and promoting empathy and understanding. The article concludes by calling on the people of the United States to observe National Arts and Humanities Month with appropriate programs and activities.